.TH "ubi_register_volume_notifier" 9 "ubi_register_volume_notifier" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ubi_register_volume_notifier \- register a volume notifier.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ubi_register_volume_notifier
.BI "(struct notifier_block *nb "  ","
.BI "int ignore_existing "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "nb" 12
the notifier description object
.IP "ignore_existing" 12
if non-zero, do not send "added" notification for all
already existing volumes
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function registers a volume notifier, which means that
'nb->\fBnotifier_call\fP' will be invoked when an UBI  volume is created,
removed, re-sized, re-named, or updated. The first argument of the function
is the notification type. The second argument is pointer to a
\fIstruct ubi_notification\fP object which describes the notification event.
Using UBI API from the volume notifier is prohibited.

This function returns zero in case of success and a negative error code
in case of failure.
